data.title: Red Wing Heritage 8849 6" Moc Toe Black Prairie
data.meta_description: The Red Wing Heritage 8849 is a 6" Moc Toe boot in Black Prairie leather, a tea-core leather that is brown overdyed black to yield beautiful and interesting patina as the black wears away to reveal brown underneath.  Black stained welt, white contrast stitching and antiqued brass eyelets give an updated feel to this ic
data.text:
Bottoms

WAIST: Pull the front of the pants up so it lines up evenly with the back. Measure straight across the waist. It is VERY important to be sure to pull the front completely up in line with the back, or else it will result in a smaller waist measurement, which is not the true accurate measurement.

FRONT RISE: Measure from the center of the crotch to the top of the waist.

BACK RISE: On the back, measure from the top of the waist to the center of the crotch.

UPPER THIGH: Start 1″ down from the crotch, measure straight across the thigh.

KNEE: Start 13″ down from the crotch, measure straight across the knee.

LEG OPENING: Measure across the very bottom of the leg at the opening.

INSEAM: Measure from the crotch to the end of the leg.

FRONT LENGTH: Measure from the top seam near the collar to the bottom of the shirt.

Tops

FRONT LENGTH: Measure from the top seam near the collar to the bottom of the shirt.

CHEST: Measure straight across, from armpit to armpit.

SLEEVE: Measure from the shoulder seam to the end of the sleeve.

SHOULDER: On the back, measure from shoulder seam to shoulder seam.
